Context:
The Multi-Year Accountability Agreement report for George Brown College can be found on their website, along with occasional reports on various topics of interest to the college community. The MYAA Report-Back is designed to provide information on the college's participation of students from under-represented groups, access and quality improvement strategies, and programs related to the Student Access Guarantee initiative.

For specific information about George Brown College's 2013-2014 Report Back, please contact Suzanne Dwyer at 416.415.5000, ext. 6949 or via email at sdwyer@georgebrown.ca.

The college also publishes an Impact Report which highlights their support for students, community, and industry through partnerships, collaboration, and innovation. The report can be viewed on the college website. Additionally, users can sign up to receive information about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more by visiting the college's website and signing up.

The contact number for George Brown College is 416-415-2000, and TTY is 1-877-515-5559. The email address for inquiries is ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The college's social media hub can also be visited through their website.

Please note that the information on the website is subject to change without notice and should not be viewed as a representation, offer, or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
